# HCS boundaries (pointer)

This repo has a four-ring architecture. **Live rules are in `docs/host-capability-substrate/implementation-charter.md` v1.1.0+.** This file is a pointer, not an authority.

## Quick reference

- Ring 0 — `packages/schemas/` — ontology, imports nothing above
- Ring 1 — `packages/kernel/` — kernel services; no adapter imports
- Ring 2 — `packages/adapters/**`, `packages/dashboard/` — protocol/UI translation; no policy
- Ring 3 — `.agents/skills/`, `AGENTS.md`, `CLAUDE.md`, `docs/` — workflows

## Must not

- Put policy decisions in adapters
- Add a universal shell execution tool
- Represent a shell string as canonical intent (use `OperationShape`)
- Expose audit-write endpoints to agents
- Copy live policy into this repo (canonical lives in `system-config/policies/host-capability-substrate/`)
- Commit runtime state (`$HCS_STATE_DIR` / `$HCS_LOG_DIR` layout)

## Must

- Read the charter before editing `packages/**`
- Read `AGENTS.md` for cross-tool contract
- Add canonical skills at `.agents/skills/`; not `.claude/skills/` (Claude-specific wrappers only)
- Cite the charter version in any PR that adds a capability
